          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Microplastics: They‚Äôre Everywhere",
            "use_h1": false
          }
        },
        "text_razy6f": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>From ocean depths to the Arctic tundra, microplastics now reside in food, soil, water‚Äîand in <strong>our blood</strong>. These particles don‚Äôt degrade‚Äîthey just hang around, wreaking slow but steady havoc. Unless they‚Äôre incinerated (creating a different kind of mess), the plastic you used decades ago may still be swimming around somewhere.</p>",
